Description.div: On the following pages you will be asked %System_NumberOfQuestions% questions about the work and health and safety duties imposed on PCBUs.

div.font: You will be asked multiple choice questions. Answer each question by clicking the button to the left of the most appropriate response.
After you answer the last question, you will be given the chance to review and then submit your answers.
Please note that if you exit the quiz before clicking the Submit Answers button then your answers will not be saved.

Description.div: To move between questions, use the ◄ and ► navigation buttons on the bottom right of the page.

Description.strong: Who is NOT included in a PCBU's primary duty of care for the health and safety of workers?

Answer.Description: Employees
Workers the PCBU engages
Workers whose work activities are influenced or directed by the PCBU
Visitors

Description.strong: What would the PCBU NOT be required to do to fulfil his or her primary duty of care to workers?

Answer.Description: Provide any information, training or supervision necessary to protect workers from health and safety risks
Monitor the health of workers to prevent illness of injury to workers
Provide and maintain safe systems of work
Personally supervise workers while they work to ensure they are not exposed to health and safety risks

Description.strong: A PCBU has the duty to ensure the safety of customers who enter the workplace. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False

Description.strong: What steps should a PBU perform to manage work health and safety risks?

Answer.Description: Identify hazards, assess risk, coordinate with HS representatives, review control measures
Identify hazards, assess risk, control risk, review control measures
Identify hazards, assess workers, control risk, review control measures
Ignore hazards, assess workers, control risk, review control measures

Description.strong: If it is not reasonably practicable to eliminate a work health and safety risk, what should a PCBU do?

Answer.Description: Use a hierarchy of control measures to minimise the risk
Hold workers liable for the duty to ensure work health and safety
Transfer the duty to ensure work health and safety to another party
Nothing, the PCBU must eliminate the work health and safety risk

Description.strong: What is the last measure in the process of controlling risk?

Answer.Description: Provide personal protective equipment for use
Isolating the hazard from people
Putting in place engineering controls
Implementing administrative actions (for example, work procedures)

Description.strong: What is true in relation to the assessment of risks?

Answer.Description: You should consider what types of harm could arise from each hazard
Past incidents should not be taken into account
You should not consider how many people are involved in a risk
You should calculate the probability to harm by considering whether it is necessary to perform a task
… should be used only if a risk has been eliminated
… should be supported with workplace training, instruction and information
… do not involve any isolation of hazards
… should only be considered at one level

Description.strong: When reviewing a control measure, you should consider whether…

Answer.Description: … the control measure is operating effectively and as intended
… safety or supervision procedures are being followed
… the severity and frequency of incidents have decreased
All of the above

Description.strong: What is NOT a notifiable event?

Answer.Description: An employee suffers burns to their arms, requiring immediate hospital treatment
New machinery is adopted that may increase health and safety risks to workers
A sub-contractor is killed by a falling object at the workplace
A chemical spillage occurs at the workplace, immediately putting workers' health and safety at risk

strong.strong: Complete the sentence. If a notifiable event occurs at a workplace…

Answer.Description: … the PCBU must adopt new control measures for addressing health and safety risks
… there are no obligations on the PCBU unless someone was killed or seriously injured
… the PCBU must contact WorkSafe New Zealand immediately after becoming aware of it
… the PCBU must ensure that activities at the workplace proceed as normal until an inspector has arrived
A PCBU must ensure that first aid equipment is provided to the workplace
Workers are responsible for learning how to treat themselves with first aid equipment
A PCBU must prepare and regularly test procedures to be followed in an emergency
Relevant workers must receive information, training and instruction about the planned emergency procedures

Description.strong: What must a PCBU ensure so that its general workplace facilities are safe?

Answer.Description: That the condition of the workplace enables people to move around with moderate risk to their health and safety
That the workplace is visually stimulating to create a more pleasant workplace and, as a result, avoid harm to health and safety
That there is adequate space for work to be performed without risk to health and safety
That the PCBU conducts hourly safety checks

strong.strong: Which statement is false? Any training provided to workers must…

Answer.Description: … consider the nature of the risks associated with the work
… consider the nature of work performed by the worker being trained
… be shorter than two hours in duration
… consider any control measures that have been implemented to manage risks

Description.strong: What additional duties do PCBUs have if they are involved in activities that include plant, substances or structures?

Answer.Description: Designing and manufacturing items to operate without risks to health and safety
Carrying out testing or examination to make sure that items are without risk to health or safety
Taking steps to ensure items imported or supplied are without risk to health and safety
All of the above
